    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <nav class="panel">
          <p class="panel-heading">
              Double TAP - Text and Test Anything Protocol
          </p>
          <div class="panel-block">
            <p class="control">
              Double TAP is lightweight testing frameworks where users write black box tests as rules
              checking output from tested "boxes". Boxes could be anything from http client, web server
              or messages in syslog. This univeral approach allows to tests anything with just dropping
              text rules describing system behaviour in black box manner.
            </p>
            <p class="control">
              Simple example for http web server. Double TAP code:
              <pre>
                HTTP/1.1 200 OK
                Server: nginx/1.18.0
              </pre>
              Implementation code (the one producing output):
              <pre>
              <code class="language-bash">curl http://127.0.0.1 -D - -s -o /deb/null | head</code>
              </pre>
            </p>
          </div>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </section>